      <graphic xlink:href="3101f1"/>
    </fig>
    <p>In conclusion, micRocounter provides a fast, accurate, and open source software in the R environment that will facilitate analyses of new genomes and comparative analyses of microsatellite content across genomes of many species. Furthermore, because it is in the R environment, it is simple and straightforward for users to take their results and use them in downstream analyses or visualizations that are already available in other packages. All memory usage and processing time calculations were completed on a MacBook Pro with a 2.8 GHz i9 processor and 16 GB of RAM. Scripts were run in RStudio version 1.1.442 using R version 3.5.2 (<xref rid="bib15" ref-type="bibr">R Development Core Team 2013</xref>; <xref rid="bib17" ref-type="bibr">RStudio Team 2015</xref>).</p>
